<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>File-Operation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/file-operation/</link><description>Recent content in File-Operation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/file-operation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] macOS Cocoa Error Codes (1–713)</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/cocoa-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/cocoa-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-cocoa-error-codes-1713"&gt;macOS Cocoa Error Codes (1–713)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cocoa error codes in the &lt;code&gt;NSCocoaErrorDomain&lt;/code&gt; cover file operations, data parsing, migration, and general Foundation framework failures. These codes range from 1 to 713 and are the most common errors in macOS applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key error ranges in NSCocoaErrorDomain:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;0–102&lt;/strong&gt;: File system operations (read, write, delete, copy)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;256–512&lt;/strong&gt;: File read errors (corrupt file, format issues)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;512–768&lt;/strong&gt;: File write errors (permissions, disk full, unknown)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;640–896&lt;/strong&gt;: File coordination and protection errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1024–1280&lt;/strong&gt;: Migration and validation errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient file system permissions for the operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk is full or the target volume is read-only&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File format is incompatible with the expected type&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sandbox restrictions blocking file access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-error-code-specifics"&gt;Check Error Code Specifics&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; FileManager.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;.contentsOfDirectory(at: url, includingPropertiesForKeys: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; error &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; NSError {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error domain: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;error.domain&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error code: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;error.code&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;UserInfo: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;error.userInfo&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="handle-file-permission-errors"&gt;Handle File Permission Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check and fix file permissions&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -la /path/to/problem/file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;644&lt;/span&gt; /path/to/problem/file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="verify-disk-space"&gt;Verify Disk Space&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;df -h /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reset-file-coordination"&gt;Reset File Coordination&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Force kill file coordination daemon&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo killall filecoordinationd
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="implement-error-recovery-in-code"&gt;Implement Error Recovery in Code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;performFileOperation&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; data.write(to: fileURL, options: .atomic)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; CocoaError.fileWriteOutOfSpace {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Handle disk full&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; CocoaError.fileWriteNoPermission {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Handle permission denied&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Handle other errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/nsfileerror/"&gt;NSFileError&lt;/a&gt; — Detailed file system error codes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/core-data/"&gt;Core Data Errors&lt;/a&gt; — Core Data persistence layer errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/launch-services-error/"&gt;Launch Services Errors&lt;/a&gt; — Application launch failures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Error 0x80070020 Windows 11/10 — Sharing Violation Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/0x80070020/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/0x80070020/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-error-0x80070020-windows-1110--sharing-violation-fix"&gt;[Solution] Error 0x80070020 Windows 11/10 — Sharing Violation Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Error 0x80070020 is a Sharing Violation error that occurs when a process cannot access a file because another process is already using it. The file is locked, and Windows prevents simultaneous access to avoid data corruption.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error affects both Windows 10 and 11 and commonly appears during file copy, move, delete, or rename operations, as well as during software installation and Windows Update.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>